<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ActiveImplant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Active Implant"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents a risk class C for in vitro diagnostic medical devices"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ClassC"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassD> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents class D for in vitro diagnostic medical devices"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassD> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ClassD"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents risk class III for medical devices"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ClassIII"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents the Class IIa risk classification for medical devices."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ClassIIa"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents risk class IIb for medical devices"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ClassIIb"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#Closed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a closed status for a corrective action"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#Closed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Closed"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ContaminationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a contamination risk for a risk Type"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ContaminationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Contamination Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#CybersecurityRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of harm due to unauthorized access, interference, or data breach affecting the safety or performance of a medical device."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#CybersecurityRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Cybersecurity Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DeviceFailure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Failure or malfunction of a medical device that prevents it from performing its intended function as specified by the manufacturer"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DeviceFailure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Device Failure"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DevicePerformance> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Measured behaviour or functional characteristics of a device under normal operating conditions, relative to its intended performance specifications"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DevicePerformance> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Device Performance"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DeviceSafety> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Extent to which use of the device does not expose patients, users or others to unacceptable risk under normal conditions of use"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DeviceSafety> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Device Safety"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DiagnosticError> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A missed, delayed or incorrect diagnostic conclusion or communication that represents a missed opportunity for timely and accurate diagnosis"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DiagnosticError> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Diagnostic Error"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DiagnosticRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a diagnostic  risk for a risk Type"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#DiagnosticRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Diagnostic Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#IVDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents the In Vitro Diagnostic Medical Device Regulation applicable in the European Union"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#IVDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Active implantable medical device intended to be introduced into the human body by surgical intervention and to remain in place after the procedure."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implantable Active Device"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medical device intended to be totally or partially introduced into the human body by surgical intervention and intended to remain in place after the procedure."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implantable Device"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents an in situ correction corrective action type."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In Situ Correction"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medical device intended to be used in vitro for the examination of specimens derived from the human body to provide information for diagnostic, monitoring or compatibility purposes (IVDR)." .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In Vitro Diagnostic Device" .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InfectionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a infection risk for a risk Type"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InfectionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Infection Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of physical injury to a patient, user or other person resulting from the use or malfunction of a medical device."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Injury Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InterferenceRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a inference risk for a risk Type"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#InterferenceRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Interference Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#MDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "represents the Medical Device Regulation applicable in the European Union"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#MDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MDR"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#MalfunctionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk arising when a medical device fails to perform its intended function according to the manufacturer's specifications."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#MalfunctionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Malfunction Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#MaterialRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a material risk for a risk type"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#MaterialRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Material Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Incident that did not result in actual harm but had the potential to cause serious harm under slightly different circumstances."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Near Miss Incident"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#Open> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a open status for a corrective action"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#Open> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Open"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#PatientHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Physical or psychological injury, illness, or death experienced by a patient as a result of healthcare or device use, including harms caused or contributed to by device malfunction or misuse"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#PatientHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Patient Harm"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ProductQuality> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Degree to which a product (device) conforms to specified design, manufacturing and regulatory requirements affecting safety, performance and traceability"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#ProductQuality> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Product Quality"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#RadiationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a radiation risk for a risk Type"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#RadiationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Radiation Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Field safety corrective action consisting in the removal of a medical device from the market or from use due to safety or performance concerns."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Recall"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Communication issued by the manufacturer to inform users, distributors or competent authorities about a potential risk associated with a medical device."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Safety Alert"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medical device intended to be used by lay persons for self-testing outside a professional healthcare environment."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Self Test Device"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Incident that directly or indirectly led, might have led or might lead to the death of a patient, user or other person, or to a serious deterioration in their state of health, or to a serious public health threat." .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Serious Incident" .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medical device intended to be used once only for a single patient and then discarded."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Single Use Device"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SoftwareRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk related to software failures, algorithms, or cybersecurity issues in software-based medical devices."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#SoftwareRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Software Risk"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a user notice corrective action type."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "User Notice"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#critical> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a critical severity level for a medical device risk"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#critical> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "critical"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#high> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a high probability level for a medical device risk"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#high> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "high"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#low> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a low probability level for a medical device risk."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#low> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "low"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#medium> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a medium probability level for a medical device risk."@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#medium> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "medium"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#moderate> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a moderate severity level for a medical device risk"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#moderate> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "moderate"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#serious> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a serious severity level for a medical device risk"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#serious> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "serious"@en .
# 
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#status> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a  status for a corrective action"@en .
<https://tomascp-sudo.github.io/medicalDeviceOntology/1.0/ontology.owl#status> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "status"@en .
